-- MOVES-BlackRock hires J.P.Morgan Asset Management adviser 
-- By Amrutha Gayathri in Bangalore
-- Tue Jul 08, 2014 12:50PM EDT
-- None



July 8 (Reuters) -

Asset manager BlackRock Inc <BLK.N> said it has hired an adviser from J.P. Morgan Asset Management to oversee BlackRock's $124 billion U.S.-based fundamental equity business. Chris Jones will serve as co-head of BlackRock's Global Fundamental Equity, which represents $242 billion in assets, as well as the head and chief investment officer of the company's Americas Fundamental Equity, based in New York. [ID:nBw5DZDcWa]